> These bodacious burgers are positively layered with flavor. Fry-spiced and onion-studded pork 
> burgers are topped with melty cheddar and a tangle of BBQ-spiked onion, then tucked into 
> toasty buns. A slick of chipotle aioli holds it all together, giving you the perfect, 
> flavor-packed bite. With a heap of crispy oven fries on the side, we hope you're prepared 
> for total taste bud takeover.

== Chipotle Aioli ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} with @chipotle powder{1%teaspoon} 
to taste (start with a pinch, then taste and add more from there if desired). Season with 
@salt{} and @pepper{}; set aside.

== Caramelized Onion ==

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add @yellow onion{1}(halved, 
peeled, and thinly sliced) and season with @salt{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until 
softened and lightly browned, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> Lower heat and add a splash of water if onion begins to brown too quickly.

Stir in half the @BBQ sauce{4%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest later); cook until sauce is 
warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #medium bowl{}. Wash out pan.

== Roasted Potatoes ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges.

In a #baking sheet{}, toss potatoes with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon}, 
half the @fry seasoning{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest later), @salt{}, and 
@pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> Save potatoes for another use.

== Patties ==

While onion cooks, in a #large bowl{}, combine @ground pork{10%ounce}, minced onion 
(reserve 2 TBSP minced onion), remaining @fry seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and 
@pepper{}.

Form into two patties (four patties for 4), each slightly wider than a burger bun.

== Cooking Patties and Buns ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in #pan used for onion{} over medium-high heat. Add patties and cook 
until browned and cooked through, ~{4-7%minutes} per side.

> Ground Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160º.

In the last 1-2 minutes of cooking, top each patty with @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}; cover pan 
until cheese melts.

While patties cook, toast @potato buns{2} in #pan{} until golden.

== Assembly ==

Spread bottom buns with remaining BBQ sauce. Spread top buns with chipotle aioli. Fill 
buns with patties and caramelized onion.

Divide burgers between plates and serve with potato wedges on the side.

-- For the broccoli option: Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary 
-- (save potatoes for another use). Roast for ~{15-20%minutes} instead of potatoes.